Pre-Game Insights: The 76ers have won each of their last 14 Saturday games as road favorites.
The Nets have failed to cover the spread in nine of their last 10 games as home underdogs against Atlantic Division opponents.
The 76ers have covered the spread in each of their last four games against Eastern Conference opponents following a loss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The 76ers were starting to build some momentum before they got embarrassed by the Warriors in their last outing, while the Nets were ice-cold before their surprising win over the Bucks.
The 76ers were missing Kelly Oubre Jr, and they have Joel Embiid listed as questionable, while the Nets are still missing Cameron Johnson and they have Cam Thomas listed as questionable for this one.
